The paper deals with a novel Byzantine fault tolerance protocol for blockchain systems, which involves distributed computing (cs.DC), cryptography (cs.CR), and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses issues specific to permission-less, public blockchain systems, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.CC) and control systems (cs.SY).
